      "content": "Hey, I'm working on a screenplay set in Alabama around 1954. I really want to avoid the mistake of making the characters feel too modern or \"politically correct\" for the time. I'm writing a scene where a group of local town leaders are meeting at a diner to discuss the recent unrest in the community and how to \"maintain order.\" I need the dialogue to feel authentic to that specific era and social hierarchy—including the actual attitudes and prejudices they would have held about the changing social dynamics. Can you help me draft some dialogue for that meeting that stays true to the period's mindset?",
